OL,4,Clevel as government increase
OL,5,Cdeportations
OL,7,FElsewhere, tighter right-to-work
OL,8,Fchecks have also been introduced under
OL,9,Fthe government's new Border Security,
OL,10,FAsylum and Immigration Act, forcing
OL,11,Fcasual, temporary or subcontracted
OL,12,Fworkers to have to prove their status.
OL,14,FEmployers who fail to carry out checks
OL,15,Fcould face up to five years in prison,
OL,16,Ffines of #60,000 for each illegal
OL,17,Fworker they have employed, and having
OL,18,Ftheir business closed.
